@Node Bugs "WolfPac: Known bugs and limitations"


WolfPacPPC tends to crash with a ppc.library < V45.20 when exiting the
program. So you should really use V45.20 or higher.

Sometimes a wall very near to the player isn´t rendered.

If you are very near to a wall a wrong column of pixels appears.

Walls beside the player are stretched - thats a problem of the current
rendering engine.

Bad behaviour in low memory situations.

If a window on another screen becomes active while pressing a key, WolfPac
forgets about releasing the key. You have to make the WolfPac screen active
and to press the same key again to bring WolfPac back in the "normal" state.

The statuspanel is not sized to fit the screen - maybe in a future release.

@endnode




